cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on the vulnerabilities of deep reinforcement learning models and the potential attacks that can be launched against them. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the manipulation of environment dynamics, which falls under the category of robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper includes experiments on game playing and autonomous driving, which involve computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category.
